# Stitch MCP (Google)

- Project MCP config: copy `.cursor/mcp.json.example` → `.cursor/mcp.json`, set `X-Goog-Api-Key` to your Stitch API key from [Stitch settings](https://stitch.withgoogle.com), then reload Cursor MCP.
- When the **stitch** MCP tools are available in chat, prefer them for new screens, layout variants, and component structure before hand-rolling large UI blocks.
- Never commit real API keys; keep secrets in local `mcp.json` only (gitignored) or Cursor MCP UI.

# Stitch-inspired product UI (Resolvly)

- **Feel:** Calm, trustworthy, healthcare-adjacent — not alarming; generous whitespace; soft elevation.
- **Shape:** Rounded corners (`--radius` ≥ 0.75rem), cards with subtle border + shadow on hover where interactive.
- **Color:** Cool trust palette (blue–teal primary), warm neutrals for body; reserve strong red for true errors/denial states only.
- **Type:** Clear hierarchy — short hero headline, supportive subcopy; avoid dense walls of text on marketing surfaces.
- **Motion:** Minimal; prefer opacity/shadow over large movement.
